Task Manager

Simple and extensible command-line task management system that allows users to create, track, update, and manage tasks with priorities, due dates, and tags. Tasks support multiple statuses and can be filtered, searched, or summarized with built-in statistics.

ğŸš€ Features
Add and remove tasks
Mark tasks as done
Assign priorities (e.g., low/medium/high)
Track due dates and detect overdue tasks
Filter tasks by status or priority
Tag tasks and search by tags
View task statistics
Persistent storage (JSON by default)

ğŸ§° Technologies Used

Python 3.x
Standard library modules:
argparse
datetime
uuid
enum
json (implied in storage)

Custom modules:
models.py (task, priority, status classes)
storage.py (JSON storage backend)
task_manager.py (main API)
cli.py (command line interface)

ğŸ“¦ Installation

Requirements
Python 3.8+
pip (optional for installing dependencies)

Setup
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/task-manager.git
cd task-manager


Create a virtual environment (recommended):

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Linux/Mac
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows


Install dependencies (if any are added):
pip install -r requirements.txt

ğŸ› ï¸ Usage
1. Creating a task
from task_manager import TaskManager

    tm = TaskManager()

    task_id = tm.create_task(
        title="Buy groceries",
        description="Milk, eggs, bread",
        priority_value=1,
        due_date_str="2024-01-20",
        tags=["shopping", "errands"]
    )

    print(task_id)

2. Listing all tasks
    tasks = tm.list_tasks()
    for task in tasks:
        print(task)

3. Marking a task as done
    tm.update_task_status(task_id, "DONE")

4. Filtering tasks
    tm.list_tasks(status_filter="IN_PROGRESS")
    tm.list_tasks(priority_filter=1)
    tm.list_tasks(show_overdue=True)

5. Deleting a task
    tm.delete_task(task_id)

âš™ï¸ Configuration

You can configure the path to the storage file:
    tm = TaskManager(storage_path="my_tasks.json")

Supported task attributes:

Property	Type	Notes
title	str	required
description	str	optional
priority	enum/int	converted to TaskPriority
due_date	str	YYYY-MM-DD format
tags	list	stored as list of strings
status	enum	e.g. TODO, IN_PROGRESS, DONE

